‚úÖ Post-Document Collection: ClearCharge Claims Process

1. Contract & Bill Analysis

  • Review the supply contract for:

    • Commission disclosure (or lack of)

    • Duration and rates compared to market

    • Third-party intermediary (TPI) or broker involvement

  • Cross-check the bill:

    • Look for inflated rates

    • Compare usage vs. charges

    • Match to contract terms

  • Confirm whether hidden commissions are likely present.

2. Prepare the Claim Case File

  • Compile all evidence:

    • Contract

    • Bill

    • LOA

    • Director ID

  • Draft an internal assessment summary (optional but helpful)

  • Add the case to your CRM with status: Ready to Submit

3. Submit Information Request / Complaint

  • Use the LOA to contact the supplier and/or broker:

    • Request commission disclosure

    • Ask for TPI agreements or recorded communications

  • Many suppliers are legally required to disclose broker fees if requested by the customer or their representative.

4. Evaluate Response & Build Claim

  • If the supplier confirms hidden commission:

    • Prepare a claim demand (via email or formal letter)

    • Use historical energy rates to estimate financial detriment

  • If the supplier refuses disclosure:

    • Consider escalation to:

      • Ombudsman Services (Energy)

      • Small Claims Court (for business claims under ¬£10k)

5. Keep the Client Updated

  • Notify them when:

    • Documents are submitted

    • Responses are received

    • Claims are escalated or settled

  • Update CRM status: Under Review, Offer Received, Settlement Pending, etc.

6. Handle Settlements / Payouts

  • When an offer is received or claim is paid:

    • Confirm amount with client

    • Deduct your 25% commission (as agreed)

    • Send breakdown and payment confirmation
